-- FTSE MIB Index Rises in Milan; Gruppo Coin Advances on Sales,.Fiat Drops
-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 2011-02-02T16:49:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-01/enel-green-power-fiat-generali-intesa-italy-equity-preview.html
Italy’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index 
advanced 128 points, or 0.6 percent, to 22,653.59 at the 5:30
p.m. close in Milan.  The following companies’ shares rose or fell in Italian
equity markets today. Stock symbols are in parentheses.    Fiat SpA  (F IM) fell 1.9 percent to 7.09 euros. The
carmaker’s Italian auto sales dropped 28 percent last month and
its market share fell to 29 percent from 32 percent a year
earlier, the Italian Transportation Ministry said.  Chrysler Group LLC, which is part owned by Fiat, said its
U.S. vehicle sales rose 23 percent in January. The average
estimate of analysts surveyed by Bloomberg was for an increase
of 27 percent.    Gruppo Coin SpA  (GCN IM) climbed 3.8 percent to 7.72 euros.
Italy’s biggest department-store chain said fiscal full-year
sales at its Oviesse unit rose 4.1 percent, while its Coin store
unit boosted revenue by 5.2 percent, according to a statement.  Indesit Co. SpA (IND IM) sank 1.6 percent to 7.90 euros
after rival Electrolux AB forecast modest growth in  North
America  and Europe this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adam Haigh in London at 
 ahaigh1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at   dmerritt1@bloomberg.net . 